      "rationale": "The Reynolds-Averaged Navier-Stokes equations with the SST k-omega turbulence model are standard for internal rotating machinery flows at the Reynolds numbers of interest. The Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis power-law model is the accepted regulatory model for CFD-based hemolysis prediction. Model form is appropriate for the COU. Factor not formally assessed per MRL 2 scoping."
